## IMPORTANT: NeuroVerse OS Exclusion

This MIT License applies ONLY to the How to Save the World application code, including:
- User interface components (src/components/, src/pages/)
- PWA infrastructure (vite.config.ts, manifest, service worker)
- Lesson content (public/lessons.json)
- ACE Box content (public/ace/)
- Application styling (src/index.css, tailwind.config.ts)
- Documentation (docs/, README.md, CONTRIBUTING.md)

This license does NOT apply to:
- **NeuroVerse OS** (the underlying cognitive operating system)
- Eight-Box Scaffold architecture
- Echelon Core Intelligence
- Operator Model and memory systems
- Mission Engine orchestration
- State Engine persistence
- Mode Engine cognition
- ACE Loader architecture
- Archetype System algorithms

## NeuroVerse OS Proprietary License

**NeuroVerse OS** is proprietary software owned by Kirsten Bischoff and distributed under a separate commercial license.

Using How to Save the World in production requires:
1. Compliance with this MIT License (for How to Save the World application code)
2. A valid commercial license for NeuroVerse OS (contact kb15us@gmail.com)

For NeuroVerse OS licensing inquiries, contact: kb15us@gmail.com

